# PRD: Transactional Email Notifications via Resend

## Product
Superwork – Client Portal

## Feature Name
Transactional Email Notifications

## Status
Proposed

## Owner
Superwork Product

## Last Updated
2026-02-19

---

## 1. Problem Statement

Superwork currently has no systematic, branded email notification layer. Key platform events — new user signups, project updates, billing changes, consultant assignments — either go uncommunicated or are handled manually via personal email.

This creates:
- Poor onboarding experience for new clients and consultants
- Missed handoffs between clients and consultants
- No automated recovery path for account events (password reset, failed payments)
- Inconsistent communication that doesn't reinforce the Superwork brand
- Clients and consultants operating without timely, relevant context

---

## 2. Goal

Implement a fully branded, event-driven transactional email system using **Resend**, covering every significant lifecycle event across the Superwork platform for both clients and consultants.

All emails must:
- Be delivered reliably via Resend's API
- Render consistently across major email clients (Gmail, Outlook, Apple Mail)
- Follow Superwork's brand identity (colors, typography, tone)
- Be templated using **React Email** for maintainability
- Be logged for auditing and debugging

---

## 3. Non-Goals

This feature will **not**:
- Replace in-app notifications (a separate feature)
- Handle bulk marketing or newsletter campaigns (HubSpot will be used for this)
- Support SMS or push notifications (future phase)
- Allow clients or consultants to configure their own notification preferences at launch (Phase 2)
- Support multi-language email templates at launch

