## 9. Logging & Observability

- All sent emails are logged to a `email_logs` table in Supabase:

| Column | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | `uuid` | Primary key |
| `recipient_email` | `text` | Recipient address |
| `template_id` | `text` | e.g. `AUTH-01`, `BILL-03` |
| `subject` | `text` | Email subject line |
| `status` | `text` | `sent`, `failed`, `bounced` |
| `resend_id` | `text` | Resend message ID for tracking |
| `created_at` | `timestamptz` | Timestamp |
| `metadata` | `jsonb` | Context payload (project ID, client ID, etc.) |

- Resend's webhook can be consumed at `POST /api/resend/webhook` to update `status` with delivery events (`delivered`, `bounced`, `complained`).

---

## 10. Error Handling

| Scenario | Handling |
|---|---|
| Resend API unavailable | Retry up to 3 times with exponential backoff; log failure |
| Invalid recipient email | Log error, do not retry, flag in admin dashboard |
| Template rendering error | Catch at build/send time, send plain-text fallback |
| Bounce received | Mark email as `bounced` in logs, flag client/consultant record |
| Spam complaint received | Suppress future emails to that address, notify admin |

